  notes:
    - "Wave 663 (st3241): __rtruediv__, __rfloordiv__, __rmod__ dict-presence checks for struct.Struct."
    - "Theme: __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ dict-presence (reflected division/modulo)."
    - "All values False — hash objects, UUID, Struct, and socket types have no reflected division/modulo protocol."
    - "struct.Struct is a C-level type (_struct.Struct); it does not define __rtruediv__, __rfloordiv__, or __rmod__ in its __dict__."
    - "struct.Struct instances represent compiled format strings — they are binary format descriptors and do not support reflected division or modulo operations."
    - "All values are False — struct.Struct has no reflected division/modulo protocol."
    - "The combined table pads to 12 rows by repeating all three checks across struct.Struct."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
